Barmini (50 Best Discovery and a nominee for the Tales of a Cocktail Spirit Award for Best American Bar - East) is Chef José Andrés’ cocktail bar adjacent to his two star Michelin restaurant minibar in DC. The bar offers both cocktail flights as well as a la carte options and their drinks range from classic to modern. Unfortunately, we didn’t have time to do the cocktail flight, but we were still able to sample some of their innovative cocktails like the Floral Cloud cocktail with gin, lemon, crème de violette, maraschino and hibiscus cloud, and the Divine Wind cocktail with chrysanthemum Shochu, orange liqueur, butterfly pea, citrus singani and according to them, even magic. They also have inventive bar snacks like the waffle with A1 wagyu and the bartenders are really friendly and attentive. DC may not be the most exciting city when it comes to food and drinks and this place may be on the pricier side, but it’s definitely worth checking out. Just make sure you reserve ahead of time because we saw people waiting for seats even at 11pm on a Tuesday.
Magic happens within.
The cocktail flight is well worth the experience.  Book in advance!

A totally unique culinary experience. From the almost speakeasy type entrance, it's different. We entered a white draped room before being brought into the cooking and eating room. There was a large staff of chefs and attendants, busily preparing for the seating. A total of 12 places were available at the L-shaped bar. Patrons were from multiple states and countries. In total there were over 2 dozen exquisitely crafted tastes, paired with beverages from non alcoholic to multiple levels of wine. The seating took approximately 2 hours, and included a visit to the attached minibar. Minibar offered a similar level of cocktails, plus is where a dessert vessel and the final check was delivered with its own flair. A once in a lifetime experience.
Bartender was great over all worth the time and the money. However, didn't value the reservations so stacked together that meant being kicked out of our seats and chugging our last cocktails.

Barmini never disappoints! Best mixologists around in an intimate and whimsical space. I have celebrated my birthday and others and will be making it a tradition for as long as I live in the area. Though reservations are suggested and required, I managed to pop my head in one day and find two available seats at the bar for about an hour. One day I’ll try the twenty-course meal at Minibar.

Had such a great time trying a bunch of different innovative cocktails that I would have never of thought or had the patience to put together myself. Everything was fantastic and the bartender Alex really made the experience memorable for our group. The food we ordered was great albeit slightly pricey for what you get.  Overall a fantastic evening and it's made me want to come back and try Minibar. I also really want to order the treasure chest next time as it sounds ridiculous.

With no snacks or palate cleanser in between the cocktails, the transitions were often jarring.  There are too many good cocktails in this town  for a chef as good as Andres to allow such a poorly curated cocktail flight.

WOWWOWOWOWOW  This is probably the most fantastic bar experience I've ever had, period. From start to finish, my time at Barmini was nothing short of extraordinary.  One of my friends was visiting from out of town and Barmini was recommended by one of my coworkers as a great spot to hit up for a special occasion. We arrived at 8 pm and were immediately greeted with an introductory cocktail to begin the evening.  We started with the foieffle which was incredible. The peanut butter and foie gras mixed together harmoniously and the waffle quite literally melted in your mouth.  Fresh off of the foieffle, we decided to order the waffle flight because we wanted to try the other waffles. I enjoyed all three but my favorites were the Philly and the foieffle.  The grilled cheese was also a good small plate to indulge in before drinks (or was it in between?).  I ordered the Cross-Eyed Mary and the Floral Cloud, both of which were fantastic. The Cross-Eyed Mary had a fruity whipped topping and the Floral Cloud was quite honestly one of the best drinks I've ever had. There was a hibiscus "cloud" placed on the drink before it was served to me and every time I took a sip, I was experiencing a symphony of smell (hibiscus) and taste (the floral drink) all at once.  My friend ordered the Divine Wind and one of the tiki cocktails. Both were very good. We were also given some sort of other drink served in a rocket ship which was out of this world. Sorry, I had to make the joke.  Prices are steep for the drinks but I think the experience was totally worth it.

Definitely the best of the craft cocktail genre in DC. Is it fussy? Yes. There is extreme attention to detail, hyper knowledgeable staff, and an overly curated collection of weird seating and tchotchkes. But the options are a myriad of spirits, visual and taste combinations, and delivery. The staff know what they are doing. The space is comfortable and interesting (and offers many Instagram opportunities). I have never had a bad experience here, but one should recognize that it is less a bar and more like going to a restaurant. You are out when your reservation ends. The bar menu is small, but offers an interesting variety. Not many vegan options and you aren't going to get full here (unless you want to spend a lot of money). Plan to go before or after dinner. And definitely plan to go.

Delicious cocktails and small bites. Very pricey but high quality cocktails. This is a nice place to celebrate a special event. I wish they would fix the machine that makes the Veruca Salt Cocktail.

Excellent cocktail lab. Modern style and fabulously crafted drinks. The classics are great, but get the ones created only at Barmini. Wait staff is consistently great. Amazing wagyu philly cheese waffle and great grilled cheese. Be prepared to fall in love with this Jose Andres spot!
What an amazing place for drinks! Call way ahead of your occasion to make sure you can get a reservation. It's semi-intimate and biz casual. The food options are also very good and change regularly.

Trying out Barmini for the first time last weekend really was something else.  Just walking into the bar, the sheer atmosphere was that of a really fun laboratory. I saw a bartender making cocktails that smoked so much it looked like they had dry ice in them, and he had a whole mad scientist getup. It was a joy watching him make my cocktail to tell you the truth, just the presentation alone lead me to believe that this was a great cocktail even before I tried it. The service was also stellar. My only complaint is really about the food.  The food isn't exactly the cheapest stuff around and that is a bit of bummer because I got what felt like appetizers when I felt like I had paid enough for a huge quarter pounder.

This is a small space adjoining minibar that holds roughly 20 people at a bar or some odd seating. They have a large list of delicious cocktails. They started us with a small "welcome" cocktail that had a cucumber flavor. The cocktail menu is extensive (roughly 100 maybe?). The ones I tried were very smooth but the pumpkin one I had barely tasted like pumpkin. The appetizer plates were delicious such as the liquid olive and grilled cheese. The service was excellent and very friendly. Overall, a solid way to experience a small bit of the more expensive sister place next door.

Wow. Talk about the most amazing lounge ever. Super modern insides with eclectic glasses and perfectly executed cocktails. Classy as all hell and the tapas they serve are to die for. Highly recommended. #dishcrawlapproved

A great place for artisanal cocktails. They have an extensive cocktail list and every drink our group ordered was delicious. However I wouldn't go in with the expectations for fine dining experience as most dishes are more like upscale bar food. The food menu clearly shows its effort of bringing in interesting twists and probably resonating the experience next door at mini bar. But some soundingly interesting dishes came out rather underwhelming like the uni panini and lobster roll. Not sure if i would bother with the troublesome reservation process here on a regular basis, but I'd recommend if there's a special occasion or you have a foodie guest in town and you want to show them the dc dining experience.

TIP: for reservations call the bar for last minute cancellations or the usual booking weeks in advance. Worth the wait though. We came over here for some cocktails and to try their innovative tapas. I went for a double rum combination (double something) and I must say it was quite on the top (maybe too much alcohol for me). We ordered the lobster roll (yummy) and the cheese sandwich. I did love the lab ambiance as well as the exquisite service (a bit too snooty at the beginning). This is the perfect place to come with friends, sit and enjoy the drinks.
